l=https://brickset.com/sets/theme-Collectable-Minifigures/subtheme-Series-06|website=Brickset|accessdate=18 March 2018}}</ref>\n{| class=\"sortable wikitable\" cellpadding=\"5\" style=\"font-size:90%; text-align:center; margin: 1em auto 1em auto\" style=\"\n|-\n! style=\"width:1em;\"  | #\n! style=\"width:15em;\" | Minifigure\n! style=\"width:20em;\" | Accessories\n! class=\"unsortable\"  | Notes\n|-\n|1\n|[[Grey alien|Classic Alien]]||[[Raygun]]||Based on a [[Grey alien]]. First appearance of the Grey alien head piece.\n|-\n|2\n|[[William Wallace|Highland Battler]]||[[Sword]], [[Shield]]|| This minifigure is a reference to [[William Wallace]]\n|-\n|3\n|[[Sleepover|Sleepyhead]]||[[Teddy bear]]||First appearance of the Lego teddy bear piece.\n|-\n|4\n|[[Statue of Liberty|Lady Liberty]]||[[Torch]], ''[[Tabula ansata]]''||First appearance of the Lego Lady Liberty hair and crow combination piece. The plate has \"JULY IV MDCCLXXVI\" written on it.\n|-\n|5\n|[[Black and white hat symbolism in film|Bandit]]||[[Revolver]] (2)||This minifigure is a direct reference to the \"Bandit\" Lego Western sub-theme.\n|-\n|6\n|[[Flamenco]] Dancer||[[Hand fan]]||First appearance of the Lego short styled hair piece. \n|-\n|7\n|[[Tin toy|Clockwork Robot]]||||First appearance of the Lego clockwork head and windup pieces.\n|-\n|8\n|[[Minotaur]]||[[Battle axe]]||First appearance of the Lego minotaur head piece.\n|-\n|9\n|[[Leprechaun]]||Pot of gold||First appearance of the Lego small pot piece. \n|-\n|10\n|[[Roman legion|Roman Soldier]]||[[Spear]], Shield||First appearance of the Lego Roman shield piece. \n|-\n|11\n|Surgeon||[[X-ray]], [[Hypodermic needle|Needle]]||First appearance of the Lego surgeon hat piece. \n|-\n|12\n|[[Skateboarding|Skater]] Girl||[[Skateboard]]|| \n|-\n|13\n|[[List of female action heroes and villains|Intergalactic Girl]]||Raygun||This minifigure is a direct reference to the \"Classic Space\" Lego Space sub-theme. A female variant of the Spaceman (Series 1).\n|-\n|14\n|Butcher||[[T-bone steak]], [[Cleaver]]||First appearance of the Lego T-bone piece.\n|-\n|15\n|[[Auto mechanic|Mechanic]]||[[Wrench]], [[Toolbox]]||First appearance of the Lego greaser hair piece.\n|-\n|16\n|[[Jinn|Genie]]||[[Magic (paranormal)|Magic]] [[Oil lamp|lamp]]||First appearance of the Lego genie hat, leg, and lamp pieces. \n|}\n\n===Series 7===\nSeries 7 (set number: 8831) was released in May 2012. The seventh series consists of the following units:<ref>{{cite web|title=Collectable Minifigures: Series 07|url=https://brickset.com/sets/theme-Collectable-Minifigures/subtheme-Series-07|website=Brickset|accessdate=18 March 2018}}</ref>\n{| class=\"sortable wikitable\" cellpadding=\"5\" style=\"font-size:90%; text-align:center; margin: 1em auto 1em auto\" style=\"\n|-\n! style=\"width:1em;\"  | #\n! style=\"width:15em;\" | Minifigure\n! style=\"width:20em;\" | Accessories\n! class=\"unsortable\"  | Notes\n|-\n|1\n|Swimming Champion||||First appearance of the Lego swimming cap and medal pieces.\n|-\n|2\n|[[Eagle warrior|Aztec Warrior]]||[[Spear]], [[Shield]]||First appearance of the Lego eagle warrior headdress piece.\n|-\n|3\n|[[Rabbit|Bunny]] Suit Guy||Carrot||A Minifigure in a rabbit suit. First appearance of the Lego rabbit hat, carrot, and stem pieces.\n|-\n|4\n|[[Bride]]||[[Flower]]s||First appearance of the Lego tiara and veil pieces.\n|-\n|5\n|[[Triton (mythology)|Ocean King]]||[[Trident]]||First appearance of the Lego Triton hair and crown combination and trident pieces.\n|-\n|6\n|[[Bagpipes|Bagpiper]]||[[Bagpipes]]||First appearance of the Lego bagpipe and bagpiper hat pieces. \n|-\n|7\n|[[Evel Knievel|Daredevil]]||||\n|-\n|8\n|[[Space marine|Galaxy Patrol]]||[[Pistol]]||This minifigure is a direct reference to the \"Classic Space\" Lego Space sub-theme.\n|-\n|9\n|[[Tennis]] Ace||[[Racket (sports equipment)|Tennis racket]]|| \n|-\n|10\n|Jungle Boy||[[Common chimpanzee|Chimpanzee]], [[Knife]]||Modeled after [[Tarzan]].\n|-\n|11\n|[[Hippie]]||Flowers||First appearance of the hippie long hair piece.\n|-\n|12\n|[[Programmer|Computer Programmer]]||Laptop, [[Mug]]||First appearance of the combed hair piece.\n|-\n|13\n|[[Shield-maiden|Viking Woman]]||[[Viking sword|Sword]], Shield||This minifigure is a direct reference to the \"Vikings\" Lego theme. A female variant of the Viking (Series 3).\n|-\n|14\n|[[Black knight|Evil Knight]]||[[Sword]], Shield||This minifigure is a reference to the \"Fright Knights\", \"Knights' Kingdom\", and \"Knights' Kingdom II\" Lego Castle sub-themes.\n|-\n|15\n|[[List of female rock singers|Rocker Girl]]||Electric guitar||A female variant of the Pink Rocker (Series 4). First appearance of the rocker hair piece.\n|-\n|16\n|Grandma Visitor||[[Basket]]||Modeled after [[Little Red Riding Hood]].\n|}\n\n===Team GB Olympic Series===\nTo commemorate the [[London 2012|London Olympic games]], an exclusive series of minifigures was released exclusively in the United Kingdom to mark the opening of the Olympics.<br />\nThis series (set number: 8909) was released in July 2012. This series consists of the following 9 units (rather than the typical 16):<ref>{{cite web|title=Collectable Minifigures: Team GB|url=https://brickset.com/sets/theme-Collectable-Minifigures/subtheme-Team-GB|website=Brickset|accessdate=18 March 2018}}</ref>\n{| class=\"sortable wikitable\" cellpadding=\"5\" style=\"font-size:90%; text-align:center; margin: 1em auto 1em auto\" style=\"\n|-\n! style=\"width:1em;\"  | #\n! style=\"width:15em;\" | Minifigure\n! style=\"width:20em;\" | Accessories\n! class=\"unsortable\"  | Notes\n|-\n|1\n|[[Archery at the Summer Olympics|Agile Archer]]||[[Bow and arrow]]||\n|-\n|2\n|[[Boxing at the Summer Olympics|Brawny Boxer]]||||\n|-\n|3\n|[[Gymnastics at the Summer Olympics|Flexible Gymnast]]||[[Balance beam]]|| \n|-\n|4\n|[[Judo at the Summer Olympics|Judo Fighter]]||||\n|-\n|5\n|[[Tennis at the Summer Olympics|Tactical Tennis Player]]||[[Racket (sports equipment)|Tennis racket]]|| \n|-\n|6\n|[[Weightlifting at the Summer Olympics|Wondrous Weightlifter]]||[[Barbell]]|| \n|-\n|7\n|[[Athletics at the Summer Olympics|Relay Runner]]||[[Relay race|Baton]]|| \n|-\n|8\n|[[Swimming at the Summer Olympics|Stealth Swimmer]]||||\n|-\n|9\n|[[Equestrian at the Summer Olympics|Horseback Rider]]||||\n|}\n\n===Series 8===\nSeries 8 (set number: 8833) was released in September 2012. This series consists of the following units:<ref>{{cite web|title=Collectable Minifigures: Series 08|url=https://brickset.com/sets/theme-Collectable-Minifigures/subtheme-Series-08|website=Brickset|accessdate=18 March 2018}}</ref>\n{| class=\"sortable wikitable\" cellpadding=\"5\" style=\"font-size:90%; text-align:center; margin: 1em auto 1em auto\" style=\"\n|-\n! style=\"width:1em;\"  | #\n! style=\"width:15em;\" | Minifigure\n! style=\"width:20em;\" | Accessories\n! class=\"unsortable\"  | Notes\n|-\n|1\n|[[Laws of robotics|Evil Robot]]||[[Raygun]]||A variant of the Robot (Series 1).\n|-\n|2\n|[[Conquistador]]||[[Rapier]]|| \n|-\n|3\n|[[Lederhosen]] Guy||[[Pretzel]]||First appearance of the Lego pretzel piece.\n|-\n|4\n|[[Cowboy|Cowgirl]]||[[Lasso]]||This skin is a direct reference to the \"Cowboy\" Lego Western sub-theme. First appearance of the Cowboy hat and long hair combination piece.\n|-\n|5\n|[[American football|Football]] Player||[[Trophy]]||\n|-\n|6\n|[[Diving suit|Diver]]||[[Speargun]]||First appearance of the Lego classic diver helmet piece.\n|-\n|7\n|[[Alpine skiing|Downhill Skier]]||[[Ski]] (2), [[Ski pole]] (2)|| \n|-\n|8\n|Businessman||[[Briefcase]], Newspaper|| \n|-\n|9\n|[[Fairy]]||[[Wand]]|| \n|-\n|10\n|[[Santa Claus]]||[[Bag|Sack]]||First appearance of the Lego Santa hat piece.\n|-\n|11\n|[[Vampire bat]]||||Reuses the design (now in black) of Manbat from the \"Monster Fighters\" Lego theme.\n|-\n|12\n|DJ||[[Gramophone record|Record disc]], Record disc case|| \n|-\n|13\n|Red [[Cheerleading|Cheerleader]]||[[Pom-pom]] (2)||A variant of the Cheerleader (Series 1). \n|-\n|14\n|Th