ainess]]||Raygun||This minifigure is a direct reference to the \"Alien Conquest\" Lego theme (a female version of the Alien Commander).\n|}\n\n===Series 9===\nSeries 9 (set number: 71000) was released in late October 2012 in the UK and January 2013 in the US. This series consists of the following units:<ref>{{cite web|title=Collectable Minifigures: Series 09|url=https://brickset.com/sets/theme-Collectable-Minifigures/subtheme-Series-09|website=Brickset|accessdate=18 March 2018}}</ref>\n{| class=\"sortable wikitable\" cellpadding=\"5\" style=\"font-size:90%; text-align:center; margin: 1em auto 1em auto\" style=\"\n|-\n! style=\"width:1em;\"  | #\n! style=\"width:15em;\" | Minifigure\n! style=\"width:20em;\" | Accessories\n! class=\"unsortable\"  | Notes\n|-\n|1\n|[[Waiting staff|Waiter]]||[[Tray]], [[Bottle]]||\n|-\n|2\n|[[Cyclops]]||[[Club (weapon)|Club]]||First appearance of the Lego cyclops head piece.\n|-\n|3\n|Hollywood Starlet||[[Trophy]]||Modeled after [[Marilyn Monroe]]. First appearance of the starlet hair piece.\n|-\n|4\n|[[Knight-errant|Heroic Knight]]||[[Sword]], [[Shield]]||This minifigure is a direct reference to the Lego Castle theme.\n|-\n|5\n|[[Roman emperor]]||[[Letter (message)|Letter]]||Modeled after [[Julius Caesar]]. First appearance of the Lego roman emperor hair and olive branch headdress combination pieces.\n|-\n|6\n|[[Metropolitan police|Policeman]]||[[Handcuffs]], [[Warrant card]]||First appearance of the new Lego police officer hat piece. \n|-\n|7\n|[[Fursuit|Chicken Suit]] Guy||||First appearance of the Lego chicken hat and wing hair pieces.\n|-\n|8\n|[[Roller derby]] Girl||||First appearance of the Lego roller skate piece.\n|-\n|9\n|[[Fortune-telling|Fortune Teller]]||[[Playing card|Cards]] (2)||First appearance of the Lego fortune teller hair piece. \n|-\n|10\n|Judge||[[Gavel]]||First appearance of the Lego judge hair and hammer pieces. \n|-\n|11\n|[[Extraterrestrial life|Alien]] [[Powered exoskeleton|Avenger]]||[[Pistol]]||His name is 